+ cli4a help install
Install firmware matching a semver requirement

Fetches the device's model, resolves matching firmware, and applies it. Downgrades automatically use factory-default soft and re-initialize the device.

Usage: cli4a install [OPTIONS] --host <HOST> <VERSION>

Arguments:
  <VERSION>
          Semver version requirement (e.g. "12", "^12.8", "<13")

Options:
      --host <HOST>
          Hostname or IP address of the device
          
          [env: AXIS_DEVICE_IP=]

      --http-port <HTTP_PORT>
          Override the default port for HTTP
          
          [env: AXIS_DEVICE_HTTP_PORT=]

      --https-port <HTTPS_PORT>
          Override the default port for HTTPS
          
          [env: AXIS_DEVICE_HTTPS_PORT=]

  -u, --user <USER>
          The username to use for authentication
          
          [env: AXIS_DEVICE_USER=]
          [default: root]

  -p, --pass <PASS>
          The password to use for authentication
          
          [env: AXIS_DEVICE_PASS=]
          [default: pass]

      --inventory <INVENTORY>
          Location of the firmware-inventory data
          
          [env: FIRMWARE_INVENTORY_LOCATION=]

      --offline
          Do not fetch firmware that is not already cached locally
          
          [env: FIRMWARE_INVENTORY_OFFLINE=]

  -c, --auto-commit <AUTO_COMMIT>
          Auto-commit behavior after upgrade
          
          [possible values: never, boot, started]

  -r, --auto-rollback <AUTO_ROLLBACK>
          Auto-rollback behavior: "never", or minutes

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
